"v.时常来访；a.惯常的 【英】 adj. 惯常的(happening often) 【考】 反义词：visit rarely(很少拜访) 【例】 the car manufacturer's frequent changes of models v. 时常频繁的来访; adj 惯常的; 间歇很短的 【反】visit rarely(很少拜访); shun『avoid』有争议: shun侧重故意避开危险、真理、社交等 = avoid deliberately; avoid可指避开任何东西, 人, 事. 它们的区别就在于deliberately, 但是没有字典指出frequent是否有故意的含义. 但是我会选avoid, 有例句表明avoid可以用来避免一个地方. (仅供参考) 无 frequent (adj.)  mid-15c., ""ample, profuse,"" from Middle French frequent, or directly from Latin frequentem (nominative frequens) ""crowded, repeated,"" of uncertain origin. Meaning ""common, usual"" is from 1530s; that of ""happening at short intervals, often recurring"" is from c.1600. frequent (v.)  late 15c., from Middle French frequenter, from Latin frequentare ""visit regularly,"" from frequentem (see frequent (adj.)). Related: Frequented; frequenting."
